modules.description: Provides a single function to pause execution for a specified number of nanoseconds. Works with integer values representing time durations. Used to introduce precise delays in real-time or embedded systems applications.

Provides functions to block execution for a specified number of nanoseconds and to manage a list of tasks awaiting resumption. Operates with 64-bit integers for time durations and a task list structure. Used to implement sleep behavior in network and timer-driven applications within MirageOS.
